{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_32","type":"command_execution","command":"/run/current-system/sw/bin/bash -lc 'nl -ba tests/conformance/features/run_resume_non_standard.feature'","aggregated_output":"     1\tFeature: Resume for Docs and CI Presets\n     2\t  The `run resume` command reconstructs docs_change and ci_improvement runs\n     3\t  from durable stage boundaries using the same shared engine semantics as\n     4\t  standard-flow resume.\n     5\t\n     6\t  # SC-NONSTD-RESUME-001\n     7\t  Scenario: Resume a failed docs_change run from docs_update\n     8\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"docs-resume\" using flow \"docs_change\"\n     9\t    And project \"docs-resume\" is selected as active\n    10\t    And a previous \"run start\" failed after \"docs_plan\" completed and \"docs_update\" exhausted retries\n    11\t    When the user runs \"run resume\"\n    12\t    Then the command exits successfully\n    13\t    And the resumed run keeps the original run_id\n    14\t    And the docs_plan stage is not re-executed\n    15\t    And the first resumed stage is \"docs_update\" with attempt 1\n    16\t\n    17\t  # SC-NONSTD-RESUME-002\n    18\t  Scenario: Resume a failed ci_improvement run from ci_update\n    19\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"ci-resume\" using flow \"ci_improvement\"\n    20\t    And project \"ci-resume\" is selected as active\n    21\t    And a previous \"run start\" failed after \"ci_plan\" completed and \"ci_update\" exhausted retries\n    22\t    When the user runs \"run resume\"\n    23\t    Then the command exits successfully\n    24\t    And the resumed run keeps the original run_id\n    25\t    And the ci_plan stage is not re-executed\n    26\t    And the first resumed stage is \"ci_update\" with attempt 1\n    27\t\n    28\t  # SC-NONSTD-RESUME-003\n    29\t  Scenario: Resume a paused docs_change snapshot with pending amendments\n    30\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"docs-paused\" using flow \"docs_change\"\n    31\t    And project \"docs-paused\" is selected as active\n    32\t    And the run snapshot is \"paused\" with a durable pending amendment for the planning stage\n    33\t    When the user runs \"run resume\"\n    34\t    Then the command exits successfully\n    35\t    And the first resumed stage is \"docs_plan\" with attempt 1\n    36\t    And the pending amendment is drained after docs_plan completes\n    37\t\n    38\t  # SC-NONSTD-RESUME-004\n    39\t  Scenario: Resume a paused ci_improvement snapshot with pending amendments\n    40\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"ci-paused\" using flow \"ci_improvement\"\n    41\t    And project \"ci-paused\" is selected as active\n    42\t    And the run snapshot is \"paused\" with a durable pending amendment for the planning stage\n    43\t    When the user runs \"run resume\"\n    44\t    Then the command exits successfully\n    45\t    And the first resumed stage is \"ci_plan\" with attempt 1\n    46\t    And the pending amendment is drained after ci_plan completes\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_33","type":"command_execution","command":"/run/current-system/sw/bin/bash -lc 'nl -ba tests/conformance/features/run_start_ci_improvement.feature'","aggregated_output":"     1\tFeature: CI Improvement Run Start Orchestration\n     2\t  The `run start` command executes the `ci_improvement` preset on the shared\n     3\t  workflow engine, reusing the same retry, remediation, and persistence rules\n     4\t  as the standard preset.\n     5\t\n     6\t  # SC-CI-START-001\n     7\t  Scenario: Happy path ci_improvement run completes all stages\n     8\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"ci-alpha\" using flow \"ci_improvement\"\n     9\t    And project \"ci-alpha\" is selected as active\n    10\t    And the run snapshot shows status \"not_started\" with no active run\n    11\t    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    12\t    Then the command exits successfully\n    13\t    And the run snapshot shows status \"completed\" with no active run\n    14\t    And the journal records \"ci_plan\", \"ci_update\", \"ci_validation\", and \"review\" in sequence\n    15\t    And payload and artifact records exist for all 4 ci_improvement stages\n    16\t\n    17\t  # SC-CI-START-002\n    18\t  Scenario: CI validation request_changes restarts from ci_update\n    19\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"ci-bravo\" using flow \"ci_improvement\"\n    20\t    And project \"ci-bravo\" is selected as active\n    21\t    And the ci_validation stage first returns \"request_changes\" with follow-up amendment \"tighten the workflow assertion\"\n    22\t    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    23\t    Then the command exits successfully\n    24\t    And the journal contains a \"cycle_advanced\" event from cycle 1 to cycle 2 resuming at \"ci_update\"\n    25\t    And the ci_update stage is entered twice across the run\n    26\t    And the second ci_update invocation includes the ci_validation follow-up amendment in its remediation context\n    27\t\n    28\t  # SC-CI-START-003\n    29\t  Scenario: Review rejected fails the ci_improvement run\n    30\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"ci-charlie\" using flow \"ci_improvement\"\n    31\t    And project \"ci-charlie\" is selected as active\n    32\t    And the review stage returns \"rejected\"\n    33\t    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    34\t    Then the command fails with error containing \"review\"\n    35\t    And the journal ends with a \"run_failed\" event referencing \"review\"\n    36\t    And the run snapshot shows status \"failed\" with no active run\n    37\t\n    38\t  # SC-CI-START-004\n    39\t  Scenario: Retryable ci_update transport failure succeeds on a later attempt\n    40\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"ci-delta\" using flow \"ci_improvement\"\n    41\t    And project \"ci-delta\" is selected as active\n    42\t    And the ci_update stage fails once with a transport failure before succeeding\n    43\t    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    44\t    Then the command exits successfully\n    45\t    And the journal contains a \"stage_failed\" event for \"ci_update\" with will_retry true\n    46\t    And the ci_update stage is entered twice with attempts 1 and 2\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
